<subSubSection id="2FA360CC4014466AFF768061EA84B1FE" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="670633474014466AFF768061EA84B1FE" blockId="12.[163,779,1353,1498]" lastBlockId="12.[827,1443,197,403]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFF768061E822B532" box="[163,287,1354,1375]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Small haustoriids (
<quantity id="A0419EA24014466AFDCB8062EBBEB532" box="[542,643,1353,1375]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 mm</quantity>
). Maxilla 2 outer lobe broadly expanded, roughly twice size of inner lobe. Pleon continuous with urosome; epimeron 3 smooth, ventrally curved (without hook). Telson cleft to base, strongly spinated. 
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFF768329E81CB67A" box="[163,289,1538,1559]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Etymology:</emphasis>
From Greek κρύΠτω, hidden or concealed, and Latin 
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFEC2830AE8ADB65B" box="[279,400,1569,1590]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">haustorius</emphasis>
the 
<typeStatus id="B8028DE54014466AFE158309E8CCB65A" box="[448,497,1570,1591]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">type</typeStatus>
genus of the family, from Latin 
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFF32836BE803B638" box="[231,318,1600,1621]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">haustor</emphasis>
, ‘something that draws in’. The gender is masculine. 
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFF7683B5EA37B6DF" box="[163,778,1693,1715]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">
Known species: 
<taxonomicName id="A0B948C44014466AFEA183B6EA37B6DF" authorityName="Hancock &amp; Ogawa &amp; Light &amp; Wicksten" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Robertson &amp; Shelton" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[372,778,1693,1714]" class="Malacostraca" family="Haustoriidae" genus="Cryptohaustorius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triarticulatus">Cryptohaustorius triarticulatus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(undescribed species complex; 
<bibRefCitation id="03284EB64014466AFE298397EBDCB6BC" author="Hancock ZB &amp; Hardin FO &amp; Light JE" box="[508,737,1724,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" pagination="2532 - 2547" refId="ref9502" refString="Hancock ZB, Hardin FO, Light JE. 2019. Phylogeography of sand-burrowing amphipods (Haustoriidae) supports an ancient suture zone in the Gulf of Mexico. Journal of Biogeography 46: 2532 - 2547." type="journal article" year="2019">
Hancock 
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFDB08397EBA0B6BC" box="[613,669,1724,1745]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">et al.</emphasis>
, 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFF7683D0E9CCB77D" box="[163,241,1787,1808]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Range:</emphasis>
Restricted to the Gulf of 
<collectingRegion id="A57DFDA54014466AFDD083D1EB6AB77D" box="[517,599,1786,1808]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Mexico</collectingRegion>
. Most numerous in brackish bays, sometimes subtidally on open coasts. Additional taxonomic issues may exist. For example, we found that the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A0B948C44014466AFE1E827DEBBAB706" authorityName="Bousfield" authorityYear="1965" box="[459,647,1878,1899]" class="Malacostraca" family="Haustoriidae" genus="Protohaustorius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFE1E827DEBBAB706" box="[459,647,1878,1899]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Protohaustorius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be polyphyletic, with 
<taxonomicName id="A0B948C44014466AFBE085EDEC9EB0B6" authority="Bousfield, 1965" authorityName="Bousfield" authorityYear="1965" box="[1077,1443,197,219]" class="Malacostraca" family="Haustoriidae" genus="Protohaustorius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deichmanne">
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFBE085EDEDD5B0B7" box="[1077,1256,197,219]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Pr. deichmanne</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="03284EB64014466AFB3A85EEEC9EB0B6" author="Bousfield EL" box="[1263,1443,197,219]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" pagination="159 - 239" refId="ref9098" refString="Bousfield EL. 1965. Haustoriidae of New England (Crustacea: Amphipoda). Proceedings of the United States National Museum 117: 159 - 239." type="journal article" year="1965">Bousfield, 1965</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
grouping within the 
<taxonomicName id="A0B948C44014466AFBFA85CFEDD9B094" authorityName="Bousfield" authorityYear="1965" box="[1071,1252,228,249]" class="Malacostraca" family="Haustoriidae" genus="Parahaustorius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFBFA85CFEDD9B094" box="[1071,1252,228,249]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Parahaustorius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade. However, without additional members of the genus and with low confidence of the phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName id="A0B948C44014466AFADA8409ED57B138" authority="Robertson &amp; Shelton, 1978" authorityName="Robertson &amp; Shelton" authorityYear="1978" class="Malacostraca" family="Haustoriidae" genus="Protohaustorius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bousfieldi">
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFADA8409EC9EB15B" box="[1295,1443,289,311]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Pr. bousfieldi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="03284EB64014466AFCEE846BED57B138" author="Robertson PB &amp; Shelton CR" box="[827,1130,320,342]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" pagination="47 - 62" refId="ref10660" refString="Robertson PB, Shelton CR. 1978. Two new species of haustoriid amphipods (Crustacea: Amphipoda) from the northwestern Gulf of Mexico. Contributions in Marine Science 21: 47 - 62." type="journal article" year="1978">Robertson &amp; Shelton, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, we suggest that additional data is needed before taxonomic reorganization is warranted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
